def_cn: 未引起质疑的；没有异议的
def_en: When something goes unchallenged or is unchallenged, people accept it without asking questions about whether it is right or wrong.
If you say that someone's position of authority is unchallenged, you mean that it is strong and no one tries to replace them.

def_cn: 未被盘问的；未受到质疑的
def_en: If you do something unchallenged, nobody stops you and asks you questions, for example about who you are or why you are doing it.
